WARRI  – Unknown gunmen have shot dead a man identified simply as the leader and command­er of Zone 2 Vigilante, Lucky Victor a.k.a. Asikolo in Sapele, Sapele Local Government Council Area of Delta State. Daily Independent gath­ered that the incident which occurred Friday evening led to tension in the area. The gunmen were said to have shot sporadically to scare the people. Suspected ‘Yahoo’ Boy Crushes Two Mechanics To Death Alleged Ineptitude: Angry Onicha-Ugbo Youths Protest Against… Sources said, “Victor was killed while driving in his Sienna car along Okpe Road close to the Licence Office.” The hoodlums drove in a tinted Sienna car without plate number with five occupants and fired multiple bullets at Asikolo. “He was killed around 7 p.m. on Friday, at Okpe Junction, a few metres away from police and military checkpoints. “Victor was ambushed by gunmen numbering about five with AK 47 rifles, after leaving the venue of the burial cere­mony of the late mother of the ex-Commissioner for Youths, Chief Omolubi Newuwumi. “The assailants drove in a tinted SUV and shot him sev­erally at close range. POLL “The incident caused ten­sion in the timber town, as businesses and vehicular ac­tivities closed immediately,” sources said. However, the Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the Vigilante Group of Ni­geria (VGN) in the state, Voke Ubuara, when contacted said they are sad with the devel­opment, saying that he was trailed and shot dead. “For the past six to seven years, criminals in the town have found it difficult to use the waterway which is part of Asikolo’s jurisdiction. “Before, when criminals op­erated in the town, the water­way was an easy escape route, but Asikolo when he assumed office became a stumbling block to that arrangement. “We will partner with the police to see how we can fish out his killers,” he added. When contacted, the State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Bright Edafe con­firmed the incident.